<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="368" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72113/596</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Alien Property Custodian</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PAM1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your letter
                            of June 24, 1918, respecting certain funds held by Swedish consuls and
                            Swiss consuls, in charge of Austro-Hungarian and German interests in the
                            United States, respectively, in which you state that unless there is
                            some diplomatic reason to the contrary you propose to make formal
                            demand, in the usual form, upon the Swedish and Swiss consuls for the
                            delivery to you of the enemy property in question.</p>
                        <p>In reply you are informed that this Department perceives of no reason why
                            you should not carry out the action proposed.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>